# Nest Checkout — Cursor Rules

## Project
A mini desktop web app for Netlight's weekly "Nest Checkout" ritual.
Stack: React + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 (Vite). No backend, no router.
All state lives in App.tsx as a wizard flow.

## Features
Wizard with steps: Start → Name/Alias → Mood Meter → Achievements & Learnings
→ Fun Question → Weekend Highlight → Overview Board.
Each participant gets a unique animal emoji and sticky note color, consistent throughout.

## Netlight Branding
See full reference: @docs/brand.md

Key tokens: bg-nl-purple (#A29AFF), bg-nl-yellow (#FFF400), bg-nl-black, bg-nl-white, bg-nl-beige
Font: Proxima Nova (all weights loaded in src/index.css via @font-face)
Always use nl-* Tailwind tokens — never hardcode hex values in components.

## Code Style
- Functional components only, no class components
- Keep each component small and focused (< 100 lines)
- Tailwind classes only for styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Use nl-* color tokens (e.g. bg-nl-purple, text-nl-yellow)
- No external state management (useState/useReducer in App.tsx is enough)
- No backend, no API calls, no persistence
- Desktop-first layout (min-width: 1024px assumed)
